div1.p:
170. 




                     GEORGE GREENLAND (49) 



                        PLEADED GUILTY



                     to feloniously forging and uttering receipts to postal orders for 10s. and 5s.;


                     also the endorsement to an order for 34l.; 


                     also to stealing while employed in the Post Office a post packet containing a cheque-book; 


                     also a letter containing an order for 35l., the property of 

                        Her Majesty's Postmaster-General
                  .—



                        Ten Years' Penal Servitude.
